        "title": "How to set parameter by name instead of its position in JDBC/JPA when calling stored procedure?",
        "body": "<p>I'm calling stored procedure from java. Now I need to set the stored procedure's parameter by its name instead of its position inidex, is it doable? <\/p>\n\n<p>I don't want to use string concatenation though, it's not safe and ugly to deal with. <\/p>\n\n<p>Notice: I need to work with OUT/INOUT parameters, too. <\/p>\n",
